Northern Ireland Election Candidate’s Home Attacked With Bomb

-- B y   C o l m   H e a t l e y
-- 
2011-03-11T09:47:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-11/northern-ireland-election-candidate-s-home-attacked-with-bomb.html
A  Northern Ireland   Democratic
Unionist Party  politician’s home was bomb early today, a
spokesman for the party said by telephone.  John Smyth is standing for the Northern Ireland assembly
elections in May. His house in Antrim was bombed at around 4:00
a.m. today with no clear motive for the attack, said the
spokesman, who declined to be identified.  The Police Service of Northern Ireland confirmed an
explosion took place at a house in Antrim, causing a small fire
in one room, without giving further details.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Colm Heatley in Belfast News at 
 cheatley@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
